# Cross-Project Memory Index

Memories that apply across every project on this machine. Project-specific
memories live in `~/.claude/projects/{slug}/memory/` and follow the same
format.

## Taxonomy (where new memories go)

Currently a flat top level plus a `tools/` subdirectory. As more entries
accumulate, organise by purpose:

- `tools/{name}.md` — external systems, CLIs, vaults, services (Obsidian,
  gcloud, gh, etc.).
- `domain/{topic}/{topic}.md` — knowledge about a product, codebase, or
  business area that spans multiple sessions. Treat as a staging area:
  when content here matures, promote it to a skill or plugin and shrink
  the memory file to a short pointer.
- `general.md` — cross-cutting writing/workflow preferences. Create when
  there's actually something general to record; don't ceremony-create
  empty.

User-level memories (identity, persistent preferences) sit at the top
level rather than under a subdirectory — they don't fit `tools/` or
`domain/`.

## Maintenance

Run `/consolidate-memory` (the `anthropic-skills:consolidate-memory`
skill) periodically to merge duplicates, prune stale facts, fix orphan
links, and surface promotion candidates. No-op on a small memory set —
pays off after ~10+ entries or a few months of accumulation, whichever
comes first.

